{"id":137,"parent_id":132,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":137,"title":"2 Corinthians 11: Paul's Sacrifice for the Gospel","subtitle":"","short_title":"2 Corinthians 11: Paul's Sacrifice for the Gospel","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-11-pauls-sacrifice-for-the-gospel","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-11-pauls-sacrifice-for-the-gospel"},[".heading",{"id":"head6","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-11-pauls-sacrifice-for-the-gospel.head6"},["h1","2Corinthians 11"],[".subtitle","Paul’s Sacrifice for the Gospel"],[".intro","Paul, like other missionaries, paid a price for preaching the gospel. Have you ever heard a returned missionary talk about the trials he or she faced while serving a mission? In",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/11"},"2 Corinthians 11"],"you will read about some of what Paul suffered as a missionary. Consider what he may have learned from his trials and how he was able to endure them."]],[".bodyBlock",[".",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-11-pauls-sacrifice-for-the-gospel.f18"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-129-3.gif"}]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f19","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-11-pauls-sacrifice-for-the-gospel.f19"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/11"},"2 Corinthians 11"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Forty stripes save one"],"(v. 24)"],["td","Thirty-nine lashes or beatings (usually with a scourge or whip)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Perils"],"(v. 26)"],["td","Danger"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","With a garrison"],"(v. 32)"],["td","Guarded"],["td"]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p68","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-11-pauls-sacrifice-for-the-gospel.p68"},"Do the following activity as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/11"},"2 Corinthians 11"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Interview a Missionary"],[".figure",{"id":"f20","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-11-pauls-sacrifice-for-the-gospel.f20"},["p.preamble","Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/11.24-33"},"2 Corinthians 11:24–33"],"with a returned missionary you know. Ask him or her to tell you about the following:"],["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","A trial he or she faced while serving a mission"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","How that trial compares with what Paul experienced"]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","What he or she did to overcome that trial"]]]],[".",{"id":"f21","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-11-pauls-sacrifice-for-the-gospel.f21"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-130-1.gif"}]],["p.para",{"id":"p72","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-11-pauls-sacrifice-for-the-gospel.p72"},"Write a short paragraph about how trials can strengthen our testimonies."]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
